editorialNotes.tagline: The tools for your first draft

editorialNotes.standard: Everyone needs a task manager—and Things is adaptable enough for anyone. This Apple Design Award winner is crisp and lightweight, featuring a simple but effective interface. The ever-present Magic Plus button makes it easy to add to-dos from anywhere in the app, and organizing items is as simple as dragging them where you want them. It’s like the unicorn of productivity tools: deep enough for serious work, surprisingly easy to use, and gorgeous enough to enjoy staring at.
editorialNotes.short: Organise class projects, assignments and daily to-do lists.
Help yourself resist distractions from your device.
Solve complex maths operations with your handwriting.

editorialNotes.standard: When we want to hunker down and type without distraction, one of our favorite resources is iA Writer. Substantially updated since its initial release, this writing app offers a customizable keyboard, selective text highlighting, iCloud sync, and many other features we’ve come to depend on. Plus, a streamlined interface lets you simply swipe left to preview a document and swipe right to access your library. The entire experience is designed to be quick and easy so you can focus on your work.
editorialNotes.short: A streamlined interface with a customisable keyboard, iCloud sync and more.
Create new notes and manage your notes better with Siri Shortcuts.

ios.subtitle: Like pen on paper, only better

editorialNotes.short: Create a mind map wherever you are and whenever you want.

advisories: Infrequent/Mild Alcohol, Tobacco, or Drug Use or References

editorialNotes.standard: Odds are you aren’t in the market for a new calculator app. But you should be. And we’ve found the perfect one: Calzy. Calzy was a 2018 Apple Design Award winner, and for good reason. The app is gorgeous on your iPhone, iPad, and Apple Watch and was built in a way that provides a seamless experience.
editorialNotes.short: Calculate with Haptic Touch and get the results in 65 languages.
Turn your ideas easily into a movie script, edit and share in the format you like.

ios.subtitle: Collect data for IISCA and SBT

editorialNotes.standard: Focus Noodles is not your ordinary focus timer. Once you’ve set a time and gathered all your digital ingredients, place your phone face down to start and let your dish cook. When you lift your phone at any point, steam escapes—halting the cooking process. (Nobody likes undercooked noodles, right?). Focus Noodles’ delightful details add fun to your productivity sessions, and with enough hard work and determination, you might even earn the title of noodle master!
